subject: Squash (Sport)
lead_paragraph: Rachael Grinham of Australia had her title defense as World Open champion end in the second round, when she lost to Vicky Botwright, 5-11, 13-11, 11-8, 11-8, in Manchester, England. Botwright is playing her last pro tournament and has already begun her job as coach at the national squash center in Manchester.
